AMAGES OR OTHER\n+// LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM,\n+// OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN\n+// THE SOFTWARE.\n+package com.microsoft.identity.client.e2e.rules;\n+\n+import android.util.Log;\n+\n+import org.junit.rules.TestRule;\n+import org.junit.runner.Description;\n+import org.junit.runners.model.Statement;\n+import org.robolectric.shadows.ShadowLog;\n+\n+/**\n+ * A JUnit rule to enable logging during a Robolectric Test.\n+ */\n+public class RobolectricLoggingRule implements TestRule {", "originalCommit": "b75a6f5d72ac6f9d4ef40cf69682348104e473b9", "replyToReviewId": null, "replies": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ4Mzc3NzM4NA==", "url": "https://github.com/AzureAD/microsoft-authentication-library-for-android/pull/1132#discussion_r483777384", "bodyText": "Ideally yes, but unfortunately we can't put Robolectric as a direct dependency in common, whenever we tried that in the past, we ran into issues so for that reason we have to put Robolectric utilities directly in MSAL, and Broker repos.", "author": "shahzaibj", "createdAt": "2020-09-04T18:08:26Z", "replyToReviewId": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ4Mzc3NjQwMg=="}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ4Mzc4MzUyNg==", "url": "https://github.com/AzureAD/microsoft-authentication-library-for-android/pull/1132#discussion_r483783526", "bodyText": "Should we create a new package that any of them can depend on, then?\nIf we can't do:\nMSAL -> Common (with Utilities) -> Robolectric\n         ^\n         |\nBroker --+\n\nCan we make it:\nMSAL/Broker -> Common\n            |\n            +-> RobolectricTestUtils (or whatever)", "author": "AdamBJohnsonx", "createdAt": "2020-09-04T18:22:51Z", "replyToReviewId": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ4Mzc3NjQwMg=="}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ4Mzc4NTAzOQ==", "url": "https://github.com/AzureAD/microsoft-authentication-library-for-android/pull/1132#discussion_r483785039", "bodyText": "The issue is that when Robolectric is added as a non-test dependency i.e. implementation instead of testImplementation then it causes some build issues. Me @kreedula tried it in the past but couldn't get it to work.\nMay be we can try adding Robolectric as a testImplementation inside common and then investigate a way to add the test src directory in common as a dep for MSAL and Broker. I think that is possible, we just haven't tried it that way. I can create a work item for that.", "author": "shahzaibj", "createdAt": "2020-09-04T18:26:31Z", "replyToReviewId": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ4Mzc3NjQwMg=="}], "type": "inlineReview"}, {"oid": "1cdb437d940616e1cb15b5f8e611dd7aa9874db6", "url": "https://github.com/AzureAD/microsoft-authentication-library-for-android/commit/1cdb437d940616e1cb15b5f8e611dd7aa9874db6", "message": "Merge branch 'dev' into shahzaibj/kusto-logging", "committedDate": "2020-09-04T18:09:57Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "4679eed3fc5cb38df5bd1ef56e5e479867e747d1", "url": "https://github.com/AzureAD/microsoft-authentication-library-for-android/commit/4679eed3fc5cb38df5bd1ef56e5e479867e747d1", "message": "Update submodule", "committedDate": "2020-09-04T18:12:13Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "814dea911020ecaf74d30996a7573137848ba79f", "url": "https://github.com/AzureAD/microsoft-authentication-library-for-android/commit/814dea911020ecaf74d30996a7573137848ba79f", "message": "Merge branch 'shahzaibj/kusto-logging' of https://github.com/AzureAD/microsoft-authentication-library-for-android into shahzaibj/kusto-logging", "committedDate": "2020-09-04T18:12:18Z", "type": "commit"}]}